SHEEP/GOAT POX - RUSSIA (SIBERIA)
*******************************
A ProMED-AHEAD post
<http://www.fas.org/ahead>
See Also
Sheep pox - Burkina Faso 980427070509
Sheep pox - Greece (Evros) 980827235532
Date: Fri, 04 Dec 1998 14:37:07 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Office International Epizooties, Paris, 4 Dec 1998
<http://www.oie.int>

The OIE's Weekly Disease Status report includes an outbreak of sheep pox
and goat pox in Russia:
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: September 1997).
Emergency report
---------------
Extract from the monthly report of Russia for September 1998, received
on 26 Nov 1998 from Dr V.M. Avilov, Chief of the Main Veterinary
Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow:
Number of outbreaks of sheep pox and goat pox in September 1998: one
(1).
Location of the outbreak: Chita region (Chitinskaya oblast), in
southeastern Siberia.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible ...
cases 801
deaths 650
destroyed ...
slaughtered ...
